              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Autumn (March to May) produces the strongest results for Durack's family buyer market. Spring from September to November is the second-best window with the highest buyer activity volumes. Avoid school holiday periods, particularly January and the mid-year break in late June and July, when the school-focused family buyer pool is less active."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How long does it take to sell a house in Durack?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Well-presented Durack homes typically sell within 28 to 45 days when accurately priced. Modern renovated homes in good condition sell at the faster end of that range. Original unrenovated homes take longer. Accurate pricing relative to recent Durack, Richlands and Forest Lake comparables is critical in this price-sensitive outer south-western corridor."
            }
